    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-27T13:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-27T13:45:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.20235/431c: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-27T14:45:00-04:00"
                            >March 27, 1944—2:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–293. The following circular airgram has been sent to all the other American
                    Republics and is being transmitted solely for your information:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of circular airgram of March 21, 1944, 7:30 p.m., printed on
                        <ref target="#pg_301">page 301</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Repeated to LaPaz, Asunción, and Santiago.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
